    <item>
      <title>About</title>
      <link>https://jen-h-lu.github.io/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://jen-h-lu.github.io/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;About Me&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;about-me&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#about-me&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I am an undergraduate Statistics student at the University of Florida pursuing research at the intersection of statistical learning, artificial intelligence, and biomedical data science.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My interest in statistics began with a simple question: &lt;strong&gt;why?&lt;/strong&gt; Rather than viewing statistics as a collection of procedures, I became interested in understanding why methods work, when assumptions are justified, and how statistical reasoning can transform complex data into reliable scientific insights.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Presentations</title>
      <link>https://jen-h-lu.github.io/presentations/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://jen-h-lu.github.io/presentations/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Presentations&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;presentations&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#presentations&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I have presented undergraduate research involving statistical modeling, physiological data analysis, and biomedical applications of machine learning.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Methylphenidate and Cue-Evoked Heart Rate in Co-morbid Alcohol Use Disorder and ADHD&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;methylphenidate-and-cue-evoked-heart-rate-in-co-morbid-alcohol-use-disorder-and-adhd&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#methylphenidate-and-cue-evoked-heart-rate-in-co-morbid-alcohol-use-disorder-and-adhd&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Poster Presentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;University of Florida CARE Annual Symposium&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Spring 2026 Undergraduate Research Symposium&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Research Overview&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;research-overview&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#research-overview&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Presented research investigating physiological responses associated with alcohol cue exposure and methylphenidate treatment in individuals with co-morbid Alcohol Use Disorder (AUD) and Attention-Deficit/Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Projects</title>
      <link>https://jen-h-lu.github.io/projects/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://jen-h-lu.github.io/projects/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Projects&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;projects&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#projects&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My projects explore statistical learning, machine learning, and computational approaches for extracting meaningful insights from complex datasets.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I am particularly interested in methods that balance predictive performance, interpretability, and reproducibility.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Interpretable CHD Risk Prediction&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;interpretable-chd-risk-prediction&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#interpretable-chd-risk-prediction&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Developed an interpretable machine learning pipeline for coronary heart disease risk prediction using the Framingham Heart Study dataset.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Research</title>
      <link>https://jen-h-lu.github.io/research/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://jen-h-lu.github.io/research/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Research&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;research&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#research&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My research interests lie at the intersection of statistical learning, machine learning, and biomedical data science. I am particularly interested in developing interpretable statistical methods that extract reliable information from complex biological systems while maintaining scientific validity and interpretability.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My current work spans physiological signal analysis, computational biology, and health data science, with a common goal of developing data-driven approaches that improve our understanding of human health.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
